dcterms:creator: Linguistic Data Consortium (LDC)
dcterms:description: The Wall Street Journal (WSJ) dataset is a widely used corpus in natural language processing, particularly for parsing tasks. It contains annotated text data from the Wall Street Journal, including syntactic structures and part-of-speech tags. The dataset is used in this paper for evaluating unsupervised labeled constituency parsing.
dcterms:title: Wall Street Journal (WSJ) Dataset
